<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - OIL COOLER and FILTER HOUSING - Installation - Oil Filter Base
        Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26509.4.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="9">
        <title>Oil Filter Base Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f2650920" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13119.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil Filter Base Assembly Gasket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new gasket set on the oil filter base.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new oil filter return tube gasket and filter housing to base seal. Coat gaskets
                and seals with clean engine oil.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter base on oil cooler cover assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650922" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter base bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install five M8 x 23 bolts, and three M6 x 23 oil filter base assembly bolts . Tighten all
                oil filter base assembly bolts to the special torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650923" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13121.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cover gasket for coolant supply port in EGR cooler</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new gasket in coolant supply port for EGR cooler and secure with two M6 x 23
                bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650924" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13122.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cover bolts for coolant supply port of EGR cooler</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten cover bolts to the special torque .</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650925" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13123.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Oil filter return tube gasket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new oil filter return tube gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650926" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13124.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter return tube</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter return tube by pushing in and rotating clockwise to lock in place, while
                aligning hold down tab with bolt hole in oil filter base. Tighten M5 x 18 lock screw to the special
                torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650927" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter housing gasket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new oil filter housing gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650928" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13126.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter housing mounting bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter housing and four M8 x 75 Oil filter housing mounting bolts. Tighten bolts
                to the special torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650929" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1366.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter and cap</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter on cap with new seal and thread assembly in oil filter housing. Tighten
                cap to the special torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall all safety guards, shields, and covers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure all tools, cleanliness covers, loose parts, and service equipment are removed from
                the engine work area.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, add oil to the engine before starting. See Engine Operation and
                    Maintenance Manual for the engine oil and filter service interval. Correct maintenance will prolong
                    service life.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <caution>
                <para>Correct oil viscosity for diesel engines is important for satisfactory operation, especially in
                    cold weather. See chart in the Engine Operation and Maintenance Manual to determine which oil
                    viscosity is best suited for the expected temperature range.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill crankcase with oil. See Engine Operation and Maintenance Manual for correct refill
                capacity.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Engine fluids (oil, fuel and coolant) are a threat to the environment. Do not put engine
                        fluids in the trash, pour fluids on the ground, in sewers or bodies of water.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start the engine and check for leaks. Fix leaks if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Shut down engine and check engine oil level. Add or drain oil to bring oil level to the FULL
                mark on oil level gauge. Do not overfill past the FULL mark.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
